<p>Note: PathPlanner isn’t responsible for any filtering or adjustment of estimated pose. The manner by which you obtain an estimated pose is a different process altogether from how you move the robot on the field, and PathPlanner doesn’t do anything for the former.</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":6,"updated_at":"2025-08-23T15:30:19.624Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":96,"readers_count":95,"score":54.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":505586,"topic_slug":"auto-alignment-inaccuracy","display_username":"Nolan Barker","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":65568,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Programming Lead, Co-captain | 3414 Hackbots"},"post_url":"/t/auto-alignment-inaccuracy/505586/5","custom_user_title":"Programming Lead, Co-captain | 3414 Hackbots","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3721767,"name":"SLAB-Mr.Thomas","username":"SLAB-Mr.Thomas","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/slab-mr.thomas/{size}/182153_2.png","created_at":"2025-08-23T15:51:53.399Z","cooked":"<p>I was composing at the time as you so I’ll piggy-back on your post. There are multiple methods to determine where the robot is and multiple methods for how to get to where the robot should be. OP <a class="mention" href="/u/kegancherry">@kegancherry</a> needs to say what their intentions are for what methods they have selected to program.</p>
<p>My team used PathPlanner to get from where the robot is to where it should be. We used LimeLight MegaTag2 plus some filtering and based on our trust in <span class="abbreviation">LL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Limelight, an integrated vision coprocessor"></template></span> we updated (addVisionMeasurement) odometry (some trust in <span class="abbreviation">LL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Limelight, an integrated vision coprocessor"></template></span>), replaced odometry (high trust in <span class="abbreviation">LL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Limelight, an integrated vision coprocessor"></template></span>), or used odometry without updating (no trust in <span class="abbreviation">LL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Limelight, an integrated vision coprocessor"></template></span>) for the current robot position.</p>
<p>This example is one of many possibilities. OP’s original code might be made to work better but we need to know what was intended so we can help describe the assumptions and restrictions and maybe make minor improvements without going down a completely different path if that’s what OP wants.</p>
